her name may be issala, but she is not dust by any means

her name is representative of Herself in the way that now it means all that she is, and not that all she is is the translation of her name

the thought that there was nothing of her soul except for dust has tortured issala for years, but i like to think that she knows now that thats not true: what was left was a place to start, if there is dust there is sand and soil to build and grow herself

eventually though, she has reclaimed the meaning of her name and become proud of it as an adult, the origins are still a sombre topic but there is no shame left in that story — why would she be ashamed now of the burden that she carried as just a young girl?

when she arrived in rivain, someone asked for her name, and all she could muster was the knowledge that now, in this new place, who she was before wasnt anything anymore, and so all that left her mouth was “issala,” for the dust that was left of her

issala chose her name at first out of self loathing & guilt for fleeing the qun — before she left, she asked her tama what happens to one’s soul when they leave the qun, to which she replied “it turns to dust.”
